{"ID":270191, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"191\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs190.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs192.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 191<\/div>\n  <div class=\"topic \">ITEMS OF INSTRUCTION<\/div>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Baptism for the Dead<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">President Joseph Smith, by request of the Twelve Apostles, gave instructions on the doctrine\n  of baptism for the dead,<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> which were listened to with intense interest by the large assembly. He\n  presented baptism for the dead as the only way that men can appear as saviors on Mount Zion.<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">The proclamation of the first principles of the Gospel<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> was a means of salvation<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> to men\n  individually; and it was the truth, not men, that saved them;<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> but men, by actively engaging<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> in rites\n  of salvation substitutionally<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> became instrumental in bringing multitudes of their kindred into the\n  kingdom of God.<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Angels and Ministering Spirits<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">He explained the difference between an angel<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> and a ministering spirit;<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> the one a resurrected\n  or translated body, with its spirit ministering to embodied spirits&mdash;the other a disembodied spirit,\n  visiting and ministering to disembodied spirits. Jesus Christ became a ministering spirit (while His\n  body was lying in the sepulchre) to the spirits in prison,<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> to fulfill an important part of His mission,\n  without which He could not have perfected His work,<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> or entered into His rest.<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> After His\n  resurrection He appeared<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> as an angel to His disciples.<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Translated bodies<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> cannot enter into rest until they have undergone a change equivalent to\n  death.<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> Translated bodies are designed for future missions.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">The angel that appeared to John<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> on the Isle of Patmos was a translated or resurrected body\n  [i.e., personage]. Jesus Christ went in body after His resurrection, to minister to resurrected bodies.\n  There has been a chain of authority and power from Adam down to the present time.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">The best way to obtain truth and wisdom<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> is not to ask it from books,<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> but to go to God in\n  prayer,<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> and obtain divine teaching. It is no more incredible that God should <i>save<\/i> the dead,<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> than\n  that he should <i>raise<\/i> the dead.<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Pardoning Mercy an Eternal Principle<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">There is never a time when the spirit is too old<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> to approach God.<span class=\"footRef\">25<\/span> All are within the reach of\n  pardoning mercy,<span class=\"footRef\">26<\/span> who have not committed the unpardonable sin,<span class=\"footRef\">27<\/span> which hath no forgiveness,<span class=\"footRef\">28<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109594\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109594)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109594)\">1 Cor. 15:29<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116089\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116089)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116089)\">D&amp;C 127:5,10<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116098\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116098)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116098)\">D&amp;C 128:1,12,16-18<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107651\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107651)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107651)\">Obad. 1:21<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110161\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110161)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110161)\">Heb. 5:12<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117191\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 117191)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(117191)\">A of F 1:4<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111554\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111554)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111554)\">Mosiah 4:8<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112648\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112648)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112648)\">3 Ne. 18:32<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109972\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109972)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109972)\">2 Thes. 2:10<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109989\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109989)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109989)\">1 Tim. 2:4<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114077\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114077)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114077)\">D&amp;C 58:27<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">7. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116706\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116706)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116706)\">D&amp;C 138:58-59<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">8. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111694\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111694)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111694)\">Mosiah 23:10<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111991\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111991)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111991)\">Alma 17:9-11<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112076\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112076)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112076)\">Alma 29:9<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">9. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116213\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116213)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116213)\">D&amp;C 129:1-9<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">10. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110129\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110129)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110129)\">Heb. 1:14<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">11. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110445\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110445)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110445)\">1 Pet. 3:18-19<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116656\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116656)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116656)\">D&amp;C 138:28<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">12. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114492\"><a hre